#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Sabbavagga"
msgstr "3. All"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Sabbasutta"
msgstr "23. All"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.23:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

#. VAR: desessāmi → desissāmi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.23:1.2"
msgid "“Sabbaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi."
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the all."

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.4"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the all?"

#. VAR: sotañca → sotañceva (?)
msgctxt "sn35.23:1.5"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuñceva rūpā ca, sotañca saddā ca, ghānañca gandhā ca, jivhā ca rasā ca, "
"kāyo ca phoṭṭhabbā ca, mano ca dhammā ca—"
msgstr ""
"It’s just the eye and sights, the ear and sounds, the nose and smells, the "
"tongue and tastes, the body and touches, and the mind and thoughts."

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.6"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the all."

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.7"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Mendicants, suppose someone was to say:"

#. VAR: vācāvatthukamevassa → vācāvatthurevassa (bj, pts1) | vācā vatthudevassa (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.23:1.8"
msgid ""
"‘ahametaṃ sabbaṃ paccakkhāya aññaṃ sabbaṃ paññāpessāmī’ti, tassa "
"vācāvatthukamevassa;"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll reject this all and describe another all.’ They’d have no grounds for "
"that,"

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.9"
msgid "puṭṭho ca na sampāyeyya, uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"they’d be stumped by questions, and, in addition, they’d get frustrated."

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn35.23:1.11"
msgid "Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmin”ti."
msgstr "Because they’re out of their element.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.23:1.12"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
